{"questionId":"13470","questionHtml":"<p>Show that the expected number of occasions per year on which Steffi visits Will’s&nbsp;house and is not fed is at least 30.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>let <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"V\">\n  <mi>V</mi>\n</math></span> be the discrete random variable “number of times Steffi is not fed per day”</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{E}}\\left( V \\right) = 1 \\times {\\text{P}}\\left( {X = 5} \\right) + 2 \\times {\\text{P}}\\left( {X = 6} \\right) + 3 \\times {\\text{P}}\\left( {X = 7} \\right) +&nbsp; \\ldots \">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>E</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>V</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>P</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>X</mi>\n      <mo>=</mo>\n      <mn>5</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>P</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>X</mi>\n      <mo>=</mo>\n      <mn>6</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>P</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>X</mi>\n      <mo>=</mo>\n      <mn>7</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mo>…</mo>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = 1 \\times 0.0416 \\ldots&nbsp; + 2 \\times 0.0145 \\ldots&nbsp; + 3 \\times 0.00437 \\ldots&nbsp; +&nbsp; \\ldots \">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mn>0.0416</mn>\n  <mo>…</mo>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mn>0.0145</mn>\n  <mo>…</mo>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mn>0.00437</mn>\n  <mo>…</mo>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mo>…</mo>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>=&nbsp;0.083979...&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>expected no of occasions per year&nbsp;&gt; 0.083979... × 365&nbsp;= 30.7&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>hence Steffi can expect not to be fed on at least 30 occasions&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Candidates may consider summing more than three terms in their calculation for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{E}}\\left( V \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>E</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>V</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD&nbsp;2</strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{E}}\\left( X \\right) - {\\text{E}}\\left( Y \\right) = 0.0903 \\ldots \">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>E</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>X</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>E</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>Y</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0.0903</mn>\n  <mo>…</mo>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1A</strong></em><em><strong>1</strong></em></p>\n<p>0.0903… × 365&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p>=&nbsp;33.0&nbsp;&gt; 30&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>&nbsp;A1AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13470","referenceCode":"19M.2.AHL.TZ2.H_10e","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Show that the expected number of occasions per year on which Steffi visits Will’s house and is not fed is at least 30.","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.7—Discrete random variables","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.8—Binomial distribution","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.17—Poisson distribution"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}